      • PrxControlSessionFilter

        public PrxControlSessionFilter(boolean filterBinary,
                       boolean filterCache,
                       boolean filterError,
                       boolean filterNoHtmlText,
                       java.lang.String filterHost)
        Create a new initialized instance.
        Parameters:
        filterBinary - filter out all URL calls whose HTTP response content contains binary data AND have a response status code of 200 (ok)
        filterCache - filter out all URL calls whose HTTP response status code is 304 (Not Modified)
        filterError - filter out all URL calls whose HTTP response status code less than 100 or greater than or equal to 400
        filterNoHtmlText - filter out all URL calls whose HTTP response content is in ASCII format (=non binary) but has another content type than text/html.
        filterHost - filter out all URL calls whose request do not match to one or several host names. Additionally, an exclamation mark in front of a host name is also supported which means that only URL calls for this host are filtered. Several host names (or IP addresses) can be passed, separated by commas (,) - with or without an exclamation mark.
